N2  - A new class of autocorrelation robust test statistics is introduced. The class of tests generalizes the Kiefer, Vogelsang, and Bunzel (2000) test in a manner analogous to Anderson and Darling's (1952) generalization of the Cramér?von Mises goodness of fit test. In a Gaussian location model, the error in rejection probability of the new tests is found to be O(T-1logT), where T denotes the sample size.
